The paper deals with topics related to computational geometry, discrete mathematics, and control theory, which are covered by the sub-categories of cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SY, and cs.GR. The first selection lemma is a fundamental result in computational geometry, which suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.CG. The second part of the paper deals with a new type of selection lemma in $\Re^d$, which is also related to computational geometry. The third part of the paper extends the weak $\frac{1}{r}$-net theorem to a kinetic setting, which involves control theory and system dynamics, suggesting that the paper could also be categorized under cs.SY. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and complexity, which are covered by the sub-category of cs.DM.
